  "description": "Swedish lecturer and docent known for his work in mathematics and physics at the Linköping public school seminar. He was born in Hälsingborg in 1905 to parents Petter B. and Bina Pettersson. He married Anne-Marie Löf in 1938, and they have two children: Gunnar (1939) and Kerstin (1943). His education includes a high school diploma from Hälsingborg High School in 1924, a bachelor's degree and a master's degree from Lund University in 1926 and 1927 respectively, a licentiate degree and a doctoral degree in 1928 and 1935 respectively. Viktor taught in several locations, including Ystad, Söderhamn, and Linköping. He has written scientific treatises." 
